div.p:
Through the grace of the Wuertembergian King I have certainly been raised to a rank which adds to my name;



      On 20 December 1867 M was awarded a Knight's Cross, 1st Class, of the Order of the Crown of Württemberg, which entitled him to add 'von' to his name.
 but while I gratefully acknowledge the condescending kindness of his Majesty, I feel that these mortal elevations render me not to that degree happy at my advancing age, as in former years.
